  "text": "Preparation and detection of the protein microarray were performed according to our previous study [CITATION_1] . Briefly, the screened protein antigens were diluted to individually optimized concentrations and robotically attached to aldehyde-activated glass slides in ordered arrays by a computer-controlled microchip spotting instrument (Cartesian Technologies, Irvine, CA, USA). Human IgG (Sigma-Aldrich; Merck Millipore, Darmstadt, Germany) was used as a positive control and an internal standard for signal intensity calibration in each test, while sample liquid and bovine serum albumin (Sigma-Aldrich; Merck Millipore) were used as negative controls.",
